This paper deals with face de-identification algorithms, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security (cs.CR) applications. The study also involves human perception (cs.HC) and machine learning (cs.MM) techniques. Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of different algorithms in preserving privacy, which could fall under the information retrieval (cs.IR) category.
